title: Sushi Zanmai D Pulze

reviews.snippet:
Famous franchise of sushi and Japanese cuisine. The yee sang is so much better than one of another sushi franchise üòõ
The food even though order small the portion still make you quite full, taste wise üëå

Really enjoyed our dining experience here. Was sat down straight away by staff and ordering was so simple using QR code. The best part was being served by a robot üôåüèΩ first time ever I experienced that and I had no complaints.

The sushi is really well priced for a tourist, I ordered so many dishes and total came to under ¬£20 (GBP). I would definitely dine here again.

Only thing to note is that the green tea is not free! I wish the waitresses mentioned this before serving us this. Would be nice if they mentioned that as the bill will be increased by RM 7 if you take it. Hence the 4 star and not 5.

Service has improved by a lot since the last time I came here. But do expect a wait during peak hours. Staff was also quite well-mannered and prompt. Food is delicious but not consistent. Some days are delicious, and some not. Cleanliness can be improved, the smell of old cloth on the table is strong in some of the booths. The portion size of their house specialty sushi has shrunk over the years.

The food was ok. My favourite go-to sushi. But im writing this review to compliment the staff there - the 2 Chinese ladies/servers and their manager (I think manager, he‚Äôs wearing a blue shirt). Very attentive, friendly, and very polite when asking/talking to me. Also took the time to explain about the voucher in the app. I am a frequent customer and their service is consistent, remains tiptop - eventhough it‚Äôs peak hour! Good job. Gonna give credit when it‚Äôs due. Keep up the good work üí™üèª

"Authentic Japanese Food"

I like the taste of the foods served to us. Sashimi, Sushi, Beef and soup is satisfying.
They also served green tea as your drink.

Place is clean and comforable.

Price is reasonable.

Food all good. Just slow. Took quite a while for my food to be served. However I was not rushing so it was okay. Staff were all good and polite.
Just one issue: When the staff was clearing the nearby tables, please don‚Äôt throw the ceramic plates into the tray. Causing such loud dishes clattering noise. Very disturbing. Please place them gently into the bus tray to avoid breaking the serve-ware.

1st - The shop needs to be refurbished
Extremely dirty-Can‚Äôt even see under the table chairs and the side.

2nd - Food was not good, coz I usually go to other SushiZanmai.
-Noodles see the presentation and you will know the taste. Look at the fried chicken so oily and cold.
-butter mushroom so sweet
-karage too much sauce

3rd - Wait time 1 hour plus, even with not full house.

See some people don‚Äôt care about all this and still go for the food, for hygiene purpose this place really need to be seriously upgrade.

As expected, the sushi is really good. First time getting the seaweed salad, it's different, but very refreshing. The Japanese soy beans, oir first time too, a little bit overwhelming and probably to try them more to get used to the very unique smell and taste üòÖ probably should have went with smaller portions. Other than that, you know it, the sushi is really tasty, fresh, and variety here. Always a pleasure to have dinner at Zanmai! üíï Enjoy the photos! Highlight of the night? It has to be the Zanmai Signature mentai ‚ù§Ô∏è

reviews.snippet: One of wonderful place to had a Japanese style cuisine especially Sushi. Glad to had one near my neighbourhood. They had a scrumptious numbers of menu to choose from,  wether you like sushi, sashimi, agemono , ramen, menrui , Gohan etc.. As a sushi lover , I'm quite surprised that they had maguro sushi & salmon belly. I hope they will be able to serve Uni (sea urchin) Sushi. Here, they served both by conveyer belt & robot server . Affordable price , tasty & had Halal certified. Will repeat.
Huge portions for one person and the tastes were surprisingly really good. The service was superb and the place is cozy. Highly recommended for lunch and dinner spot.

details.recommended_dishes: Shio Ramen with Smoked Duck, Sashimi

reviews.snippet: My first nippon sushi experience and it was wonderful. Cheese chicken was so-so, too sweet for my liking, but the crab roll was wonderful. Many selection of sushi on belt, and fast service.
A delightful and cozy spot to enjoy delicious sushi, offering an extensive variety of food choices.
Our family had birthday celebration last weekend. The cashier at that moment was very considerate and friendly. Very appreciate for your tiptop service sir.

Had iftar here, pre-ordered our food and when we came the food were already on the table. üëçüèº Everything was nice, the rice was a bit so-so. The teriyaki chicken was a bit dry but after having the sushi with the soy sauce/wasabi, it revived my appetite. üòÇ

details.parking: Can either park outside the shop if youre lucky to find one, or park at the basement. Both options need to pay

reviews.snippet: Restaurant with a view of a serene lake and has a long conveyor belt that provides non-stop sushi options. The freshly made foods, served by a cute robot came by quickly and were delicious. The restaurant was neat and clean and has a huge wall decor of Mount Fuji.

The ambience of the shop is very big and cosy.  The food was expensive as compared to other sushi restaurant but there's no selling point to justify the price. For example a bite of brownie is RM4.30 and the 5 piece Sashimi is RM20.

Overall, okay taste but you can get far cheaper at other sushi place in Malaysia.

They serving everything is flaming and all the food in the right temperature while we eating. The customer service also great. The place very clean and chill. You can see the restaurant is normal but the menu is great and many choices. Sure in my bucket list to come again.

reviews.snippet: Everything is ok, only taken on the conveyor of hard fried salmon skin, maybe it has been too long in the conveyor. The service is good and the restaurant is well managed.

Ordered sushi from grab for dinner and  they delivered some stale sushi, threw the rest away and decided not to follow up but today I have constant increasing stomach pains and diarrhoea constantly. This has affected my performance and my mood today.  I still have work to finish and don‚Äôt have the luxury to take MC as I need to finish task with a deadline soon.

Went to clinic to get meds and letter/mc as proof. Beware if you‚Äôre using grab delivery for sushi items from this branch.

Sushi king management pls pay attention and train you staff properly. I will not patronise any of your establishments again. Lack of food safety to me is a disrespect for your customers.

The staff at Cosmo Kitchen is friendly, attentive, and knowledgeable about the different dishes on the menu. They are happy to offer recommendations and cater to individual dietary needs. The ambiance is cozy and inviting, making it perfect for any occasion.

title: Nippon Sushi (Kelana Jaya)

reviews.snippet:
Arrived around 7.40pm, just about dinner time. Initially just ordered the Spicy Mala Ramen. But upon seeing how 'dirty' the soup of the Mala Ramen, we went ahead and ordered the beef curry Don.

Here's why we gave a horrendous rating.
1) ramen by nature should've a clear broth. But your Mala Ramen is dirty AF. A lot of sediments. At best, it was a soup, not ramen. Just because u added some noodles and egg into the bowl, doesn't make it ramen.
2) Your 'Don' was served on a plate. A simple Google would shows that Don is actually a bowl. On top of that, the curry itself doesn't have the Japanese curry taste, nor consistentcy. At that point, it was just a beef stew, not even curry.
3) as stated, arrival time was around 7.40pm, ie just going into the dinner time. However, the sushi train was empty, with only a handful of sushi on it. A freaking disgrace.

I am very critical about food. If you don't want people to F up nasi lemak or rendang, then Don't f up other people's cuisine too.

Compare to others sushi restaurantÔºåfor me their food is not that wow... miso soup too salty, the ebi got the rancid odour and for me the portion is abit smaller compared to others.

But thier interior is nice la...service also quite fast
Overall food is good..some innovative item like Mentai Cawanmushi and cappacio salmon. Okonomiyaki is lack of cabbage

The food was awesome.. anything u pick is quite nice and will not dissapoint you.. the problem was the service.. i came here twice for dinner around 8pm and they normally started to close around 9.30pm.. the thing is, if you close early then get the food ready faster la.. twice, we got our final receipt because they were "closing soon" but, we only got half of what we ordered.. and then, while we were eating, they were already mopping the floor around empty tables.. the second time we came, the sushi bar was late.. then, one girl staff was perli2 the sushi guys for being the reason they were closing late and the other staff was apologizing to us for the late food.. all the drama while we were eating, i swear i want to stab the shouting girl with the chopstick already.. but food was nice..
The place was a bit hard to park. But the food and services are good.
definitely my favorite place for japanese cuisine. if you go during peak hour it will take a moment before you get seated. but everything else is good here. recommended.

Friendly staff, fast service. I've been here 3 times, every time the food has been great. It doesn't taste like original sushi from Japan since it's been altered to suit local tastebud, so don't expect authenticity, but I can assure you it doesn't taste bad at all

Some of my favourites are the gyozas, mentai sushis, and tempura. Teppanyaki and rice with chicken karaage are forgettable, but they dont taste bad.

Overall, lovely place, lovely staff and lovely food.
Beef tenpayaki sedap gilaa, everything is was great !
